comments[3]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-06-03T05:05:25.739Z",codex-sdk-explorer,"Explorer finding 2026-06-03: type-preset work is canonical for batch-registering domain item types; no new item needed. Current init options are --preset governance, --defaults, --author, --agent-guidance, --with-packages, --verbose; no --type-preset or InitResult.registered_type_preset exists. A package-author-friendly PR should add preset normalization/data, idempotent persisted writes to schema/types.json (same semantics as schema add-type), folder creation after registration, InitResult + concise output + contracts/MCP/help/completion docs, and tests for agile/ops/research presets composing with --preset/--defaults and no-preset behavior unchanged."
  "2026-06-03T05:16:09.663Z",codex-main,"Evidence: Implemented pm init --type-preset agile|ops|research with persisted schema/types.json upserts, InitResult.registered_type_preset, concise init summary propagation, folder creation, CLI/SDK contracts/completion, and docs. Verification passed: pnpm build; linked pm test --run for init/contracts/completion/sdk tests; temp dogfood init --type-preset research + schema list/show + create Experiment + health; pnpm quality:docs-skills; pnpm quality:static; pnpm changelog:pm:check using pm-changelog 2026.6.2 unchanged; node scripts/run-tests.mjs coverage 2120 tests 100%."
  "2026-06-03T05:32:00.427Z",codex-main,"Review follow-up: addressed CodeRabbit feedback by asserting preset folder creation and adding init verbose/type-preset contract coverage. Existing implementation already scaffolded preset folders through readSettings after schema write; test now locks that behavior. Verification: pnpm build and focused tests passed after patch."
